<TITLE> NTV employee shot dead in Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 13 (bdnews24.com)  An employee of private TV station NTV died from bullet wounds on Friday when unknown gunmen shot him behind the RAB-2 office in Maghbazar in the city, police said. Video editor Atikul Islam, 35, was shot at 8pm as he was riding his motorcycle on way home. The gunmen took away the motorcycle, officer in charge of Ramna Police Station Daulat Akbar told bdnews24.com. Local people rushed Islam to Dhaka Medical College Hospital with bullet wounds in the chest, stomach and back. He died from bleeding at 10:15pm, NTV said quoting doctors. Akbar said they were trying to arrest the perpetrators and know what caused the attack. The incident happened hours before the Dhaka Metropolitan Police was set to launch a' special drive' against muggers and robbers on midnight Friday
